    <div class="poem">
      Yusra, in the quiet corners of my soul,
      your name blooms like a soft rose in spring.

      Your smile is my sunrise,
      your laugh is my favourite song.

      When the world feels heavy,
      one thought of you makes everything light.

      Every star in the sky feels like a tiny letter,
      all spelling the same thing:
      "I love you. I love you. I love you."

      I love you in the pauses between my breaths,
      in the empty spaces of my days,
      in all the tomorrows I have not lived yet.

      My heart has learned just one language now,
      and every word inside it is simply:
      "Yusra, I love you so, so, so much."
    </div>

